                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d603">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/799</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-12T16:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 12, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1959. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 1398. Your 1596, Embassy 2513, October 5. We adopt the recommendation set
                    forth in your cablegram and are disposed to postpone negotiations for separate
                    agreements until conclusion of general agreement, provided no great delay
                    results. We concur in the belief that there should be uniformity. In the
                    meantime we will continue to make consignments to the N[etherlands] O[versea]
                    T[rust].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
